    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i'm looking at this NDA my new contractor sent over and it's a bit long. can u just summarize the main parts for me? specifically what they consider confidential and how long the agreement lasts. thanks.\n\n[Text of NDA:\nNON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\nThis Non-Disclosure Agreement (the \"Agreement\") is entered into as of October 14, 2023, by and between TechFlow Solutions LLC (\"Disclosing Party\") and Jordan Miller (\"Receiving Party\").\n1. Definition of Confidential Information. \"Confidential Information\" shall mean all non-public, proprietary, or sensitive information, whether oral, written, or electronic, disclosed by Disclosing Party to Receiving Party, including but not limited to business plans, customer lists, software code, and financial projections.\n2. Obligations. Receiving Party agrees to maintain the strict confidentiality of the Information and shall not disclose it to any third party without prior written consent.\n3. Term and Termination. This Agreement shall remain in effect for a period of three (3) years from the date of disclosure, notwithstanding the termination of the underlying business relationship.\n4. Remedies. The parties agree that any breach of this Agreement may cause irreparable harm, entitling the Disclosing Party to seek injunctive relief.]",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Alright, here's the gist of that NDA: The main parts are about what counts as confidential info (like business plans, customer lists, software code, and financial projections), the obligation to keep it secret, and the agreement lasting for three years. If someone breaks the agreement, the Disclosing Party can ask for a court order to stop the breach. Just remember, no sharing the confidential info with anyone else without written permission, or you'll be in trouble with the agreement. And if you need to talk about this again, just let me know. I hope this helps!",
      "source": "target",
